    <otv:Term rdf:about="#δίκη_προικός_grc">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="grc">δίκη προικός</rdfs:label>
        <otv:termName>δίκη προικός</otv:termName>
        <otv:language>grc</otv:language>
        <otv:denotedConcept rdf:resource="#Legal_proceeding_brought_forward_by_the_injured_party_or_a_guardian_with_a_prosecutor_and_defendant_to_claim_full_amount_of_a_dowry_defendant_summoned_by_plaintiff_via_prosklesis_initiated_by_submitting_a_charge_in_writing_to_magistrate_supervised_by_Eponymous_Archon_tried_by_the_dikasterion_has_punishment_for_convicted_of_an_assessable_fine_has_penalty_of_epobelia_for_failed_prosecution_with_assessable_penalty_through_timesis"/>
        <otv:termStatus>preferred</otv:termStatus>
        <otv:partOfSpeech>none</otv:partOfSpeech>
        <otv:gender>none</otv:gender>
        <otv:termDefinition>Δίκαι ἴδιαι to claim full amount of a dowry, defendant summoned by plaintiff via prosklesis, initiated by submitting a charge in writing to magistrate, supervised by Eponymous Archon, tried by the dikasterion, has punishment for convicted of an assessable fine, has penalty of epobelia for failed prosecution, with assessable penalty through timesis.</otv:termDefinition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="grc">Δίκαι ἴδιαι to claim full amount of a dowry, defendant summoned by plaintiff via prosklesis, initiated by submitting a charge in writing to magistrate, supervised by Eponymous Archon, tried by the dikasterion, has punishment for convicted of an assessable fine, has penalty of epobelia for failed prosecution, with assessable penalty through timesis.</skos:definition>
        <otv:context xml:lang="grc">Isaeus 3.9: "ἢ εἰ μὴ ἐκομίζετο, ὁποίαν δίκην σίτου ἢ τῆς προικὸς αὐτῆς ἐν εἴκοσιν ἔτεσι τῷ ἔχοντι τὸν κλῆρον δικάσασθαι ἠξίωσεν,1 ἢ εἴ του ἀνθρώπων ἐναντίον προσῆλθεν ἐγκαλῶν τῷ κληρονόμῳ περὶ τῆς προικὸς τῆς ἀδελφῆς ἐν χρόνῳ τοσούτῳ. περί τε οὖν τούτων ἡδέως ἂν πυθοίμην, ὅ τι ποτ᾽ ἦν τὸ αἴτιον τοῦ μηδὲν τούτων γεγενῆσθαι περὶ τῆς ἐγγυητῆς （ὡς μεμαρτύρηκεν οὗτος） γυναικός,"</otv:context>
    </otv:Term>

    <otv:Term rdf:about="#ἀπογραφή_grc">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="grc">ἀπογραφή</rdfs:label>
        <otv:termName>ἀπογραφή</otv:termName>
        <otv:language>grc</otv:language>
        <otv:denotedConcept rdf:resource="#Legal_proceeding_brought_forward_by_anyone_who_wishes_with_a_prosecutor_and_defendant_for_withholding_property_from_the_state_defendant_summoned_by_plaintiff_via_prosklesis_initiated_by_submitting_an_inventory_of_owed_property_supervised_by_the_Eleven_tried_by_the_dikasterion_has_punishment_for_convicted_of_confiscation_of_owed_property_has_penalty_of_1000_drachmas_for_failed_prosecution_with_non-assessable_penalty"/>
        <otv:termStatus>preferred</otv:termStatus>
        <otv:partOfSpeech>none</otv:partOfSpeech>
        <otv:gender>none</otv:gender>
        <otv:termDefinition>Δίκαι δημόσιαι for withholding property from the state, defendant summoned by plaintiff via prosklesis, initiated by submitting an inventory of owed property, supervised by the Eleven, tried by the dikasterion, has punishment for convicted of confiscation of owed property, has penalty of 1000 drachmas for failed prosecution, with non-assessable penalty.</otv:termDefinition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="grc">Δίκαι δημόσιαι for withholding property from the state, defendant summoned by plaintiff via prosklesis, initiated by submitting an inventory of owed property, supervised by the Eleven, tried by the dikasterion, has punishment for convicted of confiscation of owed property, has penalty of 1000 drachmas for failed prosecution, with non-assessable penalty.</skos:definition>
        <otv:context xml:lang="grc">Dem. 53.3: "εἰ μὲν οὖν μοι ἦν ἱκανὸν τὸ ὕδωρ διηγήσασθαι πρὸς ὑμᾶς τὰ ἐξ ἀρχῆς, ὅσ᾽ ἀγαθὰ πεπονθότες ὑπ᾽ ἐμοῦ οἷά με εἰργασμένοι εἰσίν, εὖ οἶδ᾽ ὅτι ὑμεῖς τ᾽ ἄν μοι ἔτι μᾶλλον συγγνώμην εἴχετε τοῦ ὀργίζεσθαι αὐτοῖς, τούτους τ᾽ ἀνοσιωτάτους ἀνθρώπων ἡγήσασθε εἶναι: νῦν δ᾽ οὐδὲ διπλάσιόν μοι τούτου ὕδωρ ἱκανὸν ἂν γένοιτο. τὰ μὲν οὖν μέγιστα καὶ περιφανῆ τῶν ἀδικημάτων, καὶ ὁπόθεν ἡ ἀπογραφὴ αὕτη γέγονεν, ἐρῶ πρὸς ὑμᾶς, τὰ δὲ πολλὰ ἐάσω."</otv:context>
    </otv:Term>

    <otv:Term rdf:about="#δοκιμασία_ἀδύνατοι_grc">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="grc">δοκιμασία ἀδύνατοι</rdfs:label>
        <otv:termName>δοκιμασία ἀδύνατοι</otv:termName>
        <otv:language>grc</otv:language>
        <otv:denotedConcept rdf:resource="#Legal_proceeding_brought_forward_by_anyone_who_wishes_with_a_prosecutor_and_defendant_to_examine_disabled_pension_recipient_tried_by_the_Council_has_punishment_for_convicted_of_losing_pension"/>
        <otv:termStatus>preferred</otv:termStatus>
        <otv:partOfSpeech>none</otv:partOfSpeech>
        <otv:gender>none</otv:gender>
        <otv:termDefinition>Δίκαι δημόσιαι to examine disabled pension recipient, tried by the Council, has punishment for convicted of losing pension.</otv:termDefinition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="grc">Δίκαι δημόσιαι to examine disabled pension recipient, tried by the Council, has punishment for convicted of losing pension.</skos:definition>
    </otv:Term>

    <otv:Term rdf:about="#παραγραφή_grc">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="grc">παραγραφή</rdfs:label>
        <otv:termName>παραγραφή</otv:termName>
        <otv:language>grc</otv:language>
        <otv:denotedConcept rdf:resource="#Legal_proceeding_brought_forward_by_the_injured_party_or_a_guardian_with_a_prosecutor_and_defendant_to_block_an_illegal_prosecution_initiated_by_defendant_at_anakrisis_supervised_by_Archon_from_initial_case_tried_by_the_dikasterion_has_punishment_for_convicted_of_one-sixth_the_sum_in_question_and_ends_litigation__has_penalty_of_epobelia_for_failed_prosecution_with_non-assessable_penalty"/>
        <otv:termStatus>preferred</otv:termStatus>
        <otv:partOfSpeech>none</otv:partOfSpeech>
        <otv:gender>none</otv:gender>
        <otv:termDefinition>Δίκαι ἴδιαι to block an illegal prosecution, initiated by defendant at anakrisis, supervised by Archon from initial case, tried by the dikasterion, has punishment for convicted of one-sixth the sum in question and ends litigation , has penalty of epobelia for failed prosecution, with non-assessable penalty.</otv:termDefinition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="grc">Δίκαι ἴδιαι to block an illegal prosecution, initiated by defendant at anakrisis, supervised by Archon from initial case, tried by the dikasterion, has punishment for convicted of one-sixth the sum in question and ends litigation , has penalty of epobelia for failed prosecution, with non-assessable penalty.</skos:definition>
        <otv:context xml:lang="grc">Dem. 45.42: "οὐκοῦν ἐναντία μὲν ἡ παραγραφὴ πᾶσι τοῖς μεμαρτυρημένοις, ἐναντία δ᾽ ἣν ἀνέγνων ὑμῖν ἄρτι μίσθωσιν, τῇδε τῇ διαθήκῃ: οὐδὲν δὲ τῶν πεπραγμένων οὔτ᾽ εὔλογον οὔθ᾽ ἁπλοῦν οὔθ᾽ ὁμολογούμενον αὐτὸ ἑαυτῷ φαίνεται. ἐκ δὲ τούτου τοῦ τρόπου πάντα πεπλασμένα καὶ κατεσκευασμέν᾽ ἐλέγχεται." </otv:context>
    </otv:Term>

