        <otv:termStatus>preferred</otv:termStatus>
        <otv:partOfSpeech>none</otv:partOfSpeech>
        <otv:gender>none</otv:gender>
        <otv:termDefinition>Δίκαι ἴδιαι for causing financial damages related to mining, defendant summoned by plaintiff via prosklesis, initiated by submitting a charge in writing to magistrate, supervised by the Thesmothetai, tried by the dikasterion, has punishment for convicted of an assessable fine, has penalty of epobelia for failed prosecution, with assessable penalty through timesis.</otv:termDefinition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="grc">Δίκαι ἴδιαι for causing financial damages related to mining, defendant summoned by plaintiff via prosklesis, initiated by submitting a charge in writing to magistrate, supervised by the Thesmothetai, tried by the dikasterion, has punishment for convicted of an assessable fine, has penalty of epobelia for failed prosecution, with assessable penalty through timesis.</skos:definition>
    </otv:Term>

    <otv:Term rdf:about="#ἀνάκρασις_grc">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="grc">ἀνάκρασις</rdfs:label>
        <otv:termName>ἀνάκρασις</otv:termName>
        <otv:language>grc</otv:language>
        <otv:denotedConcept rdf:resource="#Legal_Stage_for_litigants_to_introduce_their_claims_and_evidence_and_be_questioned_before_the_appropriate_magistrate_in_all_suits_except_homicide_suits"/>
        <otv:termStatus>preferred</otv:termStatus>
        <otv:partOfSpeech>none</otv:partOfSpeech>
        <otv:gender>none</otv:gender>
        <otv:termDefinition>Stage of lawsuit for litigants to introduce their claims and evidence and be questioned, before the appropriate magistrate, in all suits except homicide suits.</otv:termDefinition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="grc">Stage of lawsuit for litigants to introduce their claims and evidence and be questioned, before the appropriate magistrate, in all suits except homicide suits.</skos:definition>
    </otv:Term>

    <otv:Term rdf:about="#εἰσαγγελία_κάκωσις_grc">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="grc">εἰσαγγελία κάκωσις</rdfs:label>
        <otv:termName>εἰσαγγελία κάκωσις</otv:termName>
        <otv:language>grc</otv:language>
        <otv:denotedConcept rdf:resource="#Legal_proceeding_brought_forward_by_anyone_who_wishes_with_a_prosecutor_and_defendant_for_maltreatment_of_parents_orphans_and_heiresses_defendant_summoned_by_plaintiff_via_prosklesis_initiated_by_submitting_a_charge_in_writing_to_magistrate_supervised_by_Eponymous_Archon_tried_by_the_dikasterion_has_punishment_for_convicted_of_an_assessable_fine_has_no_penalty_for_failed_prosecution_with_assessable_penalty_through_timesis"/>
        <otv:termStatus>preferred</otv:termStatus>
        <otv:partOfSpeech>none</otv:partOfSpeech>
        <otv:gender>none</otv:gender>
        <otv:termDefinition>Δίκαι δημόσιαι for maltreatment of parents orphans and heiresses, defendant summoned by plaintiff via prosklesis, initiated by submitting a charge in writing to magistrate, supervised by Eponymous Archon, tried by the dikasterion, has punishment for convicted of an assessable fine, has no penalty for failed prosecution, with assessable penalty through timesis.</otv:termDefinition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="grc">Δίκαι δημόσιαι for maltreatment of parents orphans and heiresses, defendant summoned by plaintiff via prosklesis, initiated by submitting a charge in writing to magistrate, supervised by Eponymous Archon, tried by the dikasterion, has punishment for convicted of an assessable fine, has no penalty for failed prosecution, with assessable penalty through timesis.</skos:definition>
    </otv:Term>

    <otv:Term rdf:about="#τραύματος ἐκ προνοίας γραφή_grc">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="grc">τραύματος ἐκ προνοίας γραφή</rdfs:label>
        <otv:termName>τραύματος ἐκ προνοίας γραφή</otv:termName>
        <otv:language>grc</otv:language>
        <otv:denotedConcept rdf:resource="#Legal_proceeding_brought_forward_by_anyone_who_wishes_with_a_prosecutor_and_defendant_initiated_by_submitting_a_charge_in_writing_to_magistrate_defendant_summoned_by_plaintiff_via_prosklesis_has_penalty_of_1000_drachmas_for_failed_prosecution_for_intentional_wounding_with_a_weapon_supervised_by_Basileus_tried_by_the_Council_of_the_Areopagus_has_punishment_for_convicted_of_exile_and_confiscation_with_non-assessable_penalty"/>
        <otv:termStatus>preferred</otv:termStatus>
        <otv:partOfSpeech>none</otv:partOfSpeech>
        <otv:gender>none</otv:gender>
        <otv:termDefinition>Γραφή for intentional wounding with a weapon, supervised by Basileus, tried by the Council of the Areopagus, has punishment for convicted of exile and confiscation, with non-assessable penalty.</otv:termDefinition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="grc">Γραφή for intentional wounding with a weapon, supervised by Basileus, tried by the Council of the Areopagus, has punishment for convicted of exile and confiscation, with non-assessable penalty.</skos:definition>
        <otv:context xml:lang="grc">Dem 23.22: "δικάζειν δὲ τὴν βουλὴν τὴν ἐν Ἀρείῳ πάγῳ φόνου καὶ τραύματος ἐκ προνοίας καὶ πυρκαϊᾶς καὶ φαρμάκων, ἐάν τις ἀποκτείνῃ δούς."</otv:context>
    </otv:Term>

    <otv:Term rdf:about="#δίκη ἐπιτροπῆς_grc">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="grc">δίκη ἐπιτροπῆς</rdfs:label>
        <otv:termName>δίκη ἐπιτροπῆς</otv:termName>
        <otv:language>grc</otv:language>
        <otv:denotedConcept rdf:resource="#Legal_proceeding_brought_forward_by_the_injured_party_or_a_guardian_with_a_prosecutor_and_defendant_against_guardian_witholding_property_from_ward_defendant_summoned_by_plaintiff_via_prosklesis_initiated_by_submitting_a_charge_in_writing_to_magistrate_supervised_by_Eponymous_Archon_tried_by_the_dikasterion_has_punishment_for_convicted_of_an_assessable_fine_has_penalty_of_epobelia_for_failed_prosecution_with_assessable_penalty_through_timesis"/>
        <otv:termStatus>preferred</otv:termStatus>
        <otv:partOfSpeech>none</otv:partOfSpeech>
        <otv:gender>none</otv:gender>
        <otv:termDefinition>Δίκαι ἴδιαι against guardian witholding property from ward, defendant summoned by plaintiff via prosklesis, initiated by submitting a charge in writing to magistrate, supervised by Eponymous Archon, tried by the dikasterion, has punishment for convicted of an assessable fine, has penalty of epobelia for failed prosecution, with assessable penalty through timesis.</otv:termDefinition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="grc">Δίκαι ἴδιαι against guardian witholding property from ward, defendant summoned by plaintiff via prosklesis, initiated by submitting a charge in writing to magistrate, supervised by Eponymous Archon, tried by the dikasterion, has punishment for convicted of an assessable fine, has penalty of epobelia for failed prosecution, with assessable penalty through timesis.</skos:definition>
        <otv:context xml:lang="grc">Isaeus 7.7: " ἀνδρί τε γενομένῳ συνηγωνίσατο καὶ εἰσέπραξε τὸ ἡμικλήριον ὧν Μνήσων κατέλιπεν ὅσα τε ἐκ τῆς ἐπιτροπῆς ἀπεστέρησε, δίκας δύο ἑλών, καὶ τὴν οὐσίαν ἐποίησε κομίσασθαι τὴν αὑτοῦ πᾶσαν."</otv:context>
    </otv:Term>

